          h1.display-5.fw-bold The Best Sober Coffee Shops &amp; Hangouts in Spokane
          p.lead.mt-3.text-white-75 Safe, warm, alcohol-free spaces to meet a sponsor, read the Big Book, or just exist peacefully.
          .small.text-white-50.mt-2
            i.bi.bi-calendar3.me-1
            | March 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp;
            i.bi.bi-clock.me-1
            | 5 min read

  section.page-section
    .container.px-4.px-lg-5
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-lg-8

          p.lead.mt-5
            | When you first give up drinking, evening socializing suddenly feels terrifying. The bars, the breweries, the pubs—so much of Spokane's social scene revolves around alcohol. If you're looking for a comfortable, warm place to meet your sponsor on a Tuesday night or hang out with sober friends on a Saturday devoid of alcohol triggers, coffee shops are your new best friend. Here are some of the best (and late-night) sober coffee spots in town.

          hr.my-5

          h2.mt-4
            i.bi.bi-cup-hot.text-primary.me-2
            | The Late-Night Classics
          p
            | The hardest hours in early sobriety are usually between 8 PM and midnight when the cravings hit the hardest and the meetings end. Finding a coffee shop open late is a massive win.
          ul
            li
              strong First Avenue Coffee (Downtown):
              |  A beautifully modern, bright location in the heart of downtown. With excellent pour-overs, massive windows, and plenty of seating, it's a stellar spot for meeting up after a downtown AA or NA meeting.
            li
              strong Atticus Coffee &amp; Gifts (Downtown):
              |  A staple of the Spokane coffee scene. It's cozy, slightly dark, famously welcoming, and attached to a wonderful gift shop. If you want somewhere to sit quietly and read recovery literature, this is the spot.

          h2.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-house-check.text-primary.me-2
            | The Neighborhood Hideaways
          p
            | Want something away from the hustle of downtown? Spokane's neighborhoods are packed with local roasters.
          ul
            li
              strong Indaba Coffee (Multiple Locations):
              |  Indaba is a local powerhouse with locations in Kendall Yards, Riverside, and Broadway. The Kendall Yards location sits right on the Centennial Trail—perfect for grabbing a coffee and taking a sober walk along the river.
            li
              strong Meeting House Café (South Hill):
              |  Located up on the South Hill, this cafe literally operates as a community gathering space. It has large tables perfect for group meetings or sitting down with a sponsor.
            li
              strong Brews Bros Coffee Bar (Brownes Addition):
              |  A cozy, deeply atmospheric spot in Spokane's oldest neighborhood. It is highly walkable and nestled among beautiful historic homes.

          h2.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-tree.text-primary.me-2
            | The "Not A Coffee Shop, But Caffeinated" Option
          p
            | Sometimes you just need somewhere 24/7 or highly casual.
          ul
            li
              strong The Shari's on Monroe or Sullivan:
              |  In the recovery world, there is a long-standing tradition of hitting a local diner after a late-night meeting. Ordering a slice of pie and endless cups of decaf at a classic diner booth is practically a rite of passage in the Spokane sober community. No one cares how long you sit there, and it's totally alcohol-free.

          hr.my-5

          .card.border-0.shadow.text-center.p-5.mb-4(style="border-radius: 16px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d6efd11 0%, #0d6efd22 100%);")
            i.bi.bi-people.display-4.text-primary.mb-3
            h3.fw-bold Looking for Sober Events?
            p.text-muted.mb-4
              | You don't have to just sit in coffee shops! Spokane has a vibrant, active sober community that hosts regular outdoor hikes, dinners, and events.
            .d-flex.flex-wrap.gap-3.justify-content-center
              a.btn.btn-primary.btn-lg(href="/community-engagement-sober-activities.html")
                i.bi.bi-calendar-event.me-2
                | View Upcoming Sober Events
